<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Ongar, Essex</placeName></p>
<lb/><p>My Dear Mother</p><gap agent="editorialDecision"/>
<lb/><p>
<lb/>Now, however, as I am sorry to hear your health and 
<lb/>strength are declining, and <add place="above">as</add> we are separated for some time, who 
<lb/>knows but it is for ever, a regards this worlds for we well know 
<lb/>that our time here is both short and uncertain, I now take the 
<lb/>liberty to draw your mind and direct my own to that subject which of 
<lb/>all others, concerns us most,  viz that of eternity, it is the only one 
<lb/>worth bestowing a thought upon, the subjects appear important 
<lb/>this alone is really so; our characters, comfort, businesses 
<lb/>hardships and many other things appear something, and, to our minds 
<lb/>ought to keep eternity &amp; its concerns in the background, while the fact is they are nothing, less than nothing and vanity<reg>.</reg></p>
<ab><gap extent="3" unit="lines" agent="editorialDecision"/>

